        "comment": {
            "name": "comment",
            "type": "com.atlassian.jira.issue.fields.CommentSystemField",
            "value": [
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/40497",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=lloydwatkin",
                        "name": "lloydwatkin",
                        "displayName": "Lloyd Watkin",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "The problem is the assemble() methods in Zend_Controller_Router_* classes, it is due to the way PHP's array_merge function (http:\/\/www.php.net\/array_merge) works.\r\n\r\nTake this example:\r\n\r\n[lloyd@veritas Zend]$ php -a\r\nInteractive shell\r\n\r\nphp > $arr1 = array();\r\nphp > $arr2 = array(1 => 'value 1', 'page' => 'page 1');\r\nphp > $merged = array_merge($arr1, $arr2);\r\nphp > var_dump($merged);\r\narray(2) {\r\n  [0]=>\r\n  string(7) \"value 1\"\r\n  [\"page\"]=>\r\n  string(6) \"page 1\"\r\n}\r\n\r\nYou'd expect to get array(2) { '1' => 'value 1', 'page' => 'page 1', } or similar back. Casting the array keys to strings does not help.\r\n\r\nThis means that it is not possible to use the routers to generate URIs with a numerical value using the present system.\r\n\r\nOne approach to fix this issue would be to create custom array_merge functionality which keeps the array key link even when numerical. I'll happily volunteer to create this is people wish.\r\n\r\nI'll generate Unit Tests for this issue as soon as  I get an opportunity.\r\n",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=lloydwatkin",
                        "name": "lloydwatkin",
                        "displayName": "Lloyd Watkin",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "created": "2010-05-16T04:54:49.000+0000",
                    "updated": "2010-05-16T04:54:49.000+0000"
                },
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/40498",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=lloydwatkin",
                        "name": "lloydwatkin",
                        "displayName": "Lloyd Watkin",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "Additional failing test is @ line 465 - 494 (testCanGenerateNumericKeyUri)\r\n\r\nTaken from trunk @ 2010-05-16 12:30pm BST",
                    "updateAuthor": {
